  "sourceNotes": "Apfelkuchen is one of the oldest categories of German domestic baking; recipes appear in early modern German household texts and continue through to the systematic cookbooks of the late nineteenth century. Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136, includes British apple cake forms adapted from continental originals. The chunked-apple (not grated or stewed) format is characteristic of Southern German and Austrian domestic baking.",
