  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is a cake for cooking apples when the flavour is sharp enough to push back against the sugar. Bramley, Cox, or any firm tart variety works. The apple pieces are folded in large and stay that way through the bake; you want chunks you can bite into, not a soft apple-infused crumb."
          }
        ]
      },
